## What the project is

A single-player Discord ARG where the player investigates their own disappearance.
An LLM generates a personalised missing-person case. Facts exist in four parallel
layers (truth / perceived / claimed / evidence). The player's "reality_score" starts
at 1.0 and drifts down with every action. Below 0.7 an LLM silently corrupts the
perceived/claimed layers so the case narrative starts gaslighting the player.
Three parallel timelines (investigator / shadow_a / shadow_b) run alongside.
A Journal mechanic lets the player pin a snapshot of a fact and later compare it
to the current (possibly corrupted) version with a word-level diff.

