## Known hard constraints — do not break these

- Anthropic Haiku 4.5 does NOT accept `temperature` in messages.create() — it is
  stripped in llm.py before the API call (kept in method signature for compat).
- All slow Discord command handlers must call `await interaction.response.defer(ephemeral=True)`
  as their FIRST line, then use `interaction.followup.send()` for all responses.
- All Alembic migrations use op.execute() with IF NOT EXISTS / ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS.
  No sa.inspect(), no op.add_column() — asyncpg is incompatible with introspection.
- LLM responses may be fenced in ```json ... ``` — always strip via parse_llm_json()
  in backend/core/json_utils.py, never re-implement locally.
- Session pattern: `async with get_session() as session` — commits on exit, rolls
  back on exception. Never open a second session for work that belongs in the first.

