## DB models (backend/db/models.py)

Player            — id, discord_id, onboarded_at, reality_score, settings, created_at
PlayerProfile     — player_id (PK/FK), city, neighborhood, routine, close_people, fears,
                    locations, raw_answers, personalization_intensity
Case              — id, player_id, title, started_at, phase
CasePhaseHistory  — id, case_id, from_phase, to_phase, reason, transitioned_at
PlayerNote        — id, case_id, text, created_at, fact_id (nullable FK), snapshot_value (nullable)
NPC               — id, case_id, name, description, personality, knowledge, relationship_to_missing
Fact              — id, case_id, description, created_at
FactLayer         — id, fact_id, layer_type, value, version, modified_by, modified_at
TimelineEvent     — id, case_id, timeline, occurred_at, wall_clock_slot, description,
                    visible_to_player, revealed_at, support_score, evidence_links

